ssex, England, United Kingdom":"East Sussex, England, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Ottoman Empire":"Ottoman Empire","Türkiye":"Türkiye","Paris, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Warenne was born in June 1118, in East Sussex, England, United Kingdom. He married Ela of Ponthieu about 1135. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He registered for military service in 1137. In 1138, at the age of 20, his occupation is listed as embassador to france to ratify an english-french treaty in Paris, Île-de-France, France. He died on 6 January 1148, in Türkiye, at the age of 29."},"et":{"June 1118–6 January 1148":"juuni 1118–6. jaanuar 1148","–1174":"–1174","1137–1199":"1137–1199","1118–1148":"1118–1148","from 1138":"pärast 1138","6 January 1148":"6. jaanuar 1148","1174":"1174","1118":"1118","1304":"1304","1138":"1138","1137":"1137","1148":"1148","June 1118":"juuni 1118","1199":"1199","from 1147 to 1149":"1147 kuni 1149","circa 1137":"umbes 1137","circa 1135":"umbes 1135","Surrey, England,":"Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Eskihisar, Merkezefendi, Denizli, Turkey":"Eskihisar, Merkezefendi, Denizli, Türgi","East Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","East Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"East Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Ottoman Empire":"Osmanisches Reich","Türkiye":"Türgi","Paris, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"June 1118–6 January 1148":"kesäkuu 1118–6. tammikuuta 1148","–1174":"–1174","1137–1199":"1137–1199","1118–1148":"1118–1148","from 1138":"1138 jälkeen","6 January 1148":"6. tammikuuta 1148","1174":"1174","1118":"1118","1304":"1304","1138":"1138","1137":"1137","1148":"1148","June 1118":"kesäkuu 1118","1199":"1199","from 1147 to 1149":"vuodesta 1147 vuoteen 1149","circa 1137":"noin 1137","circa 1135":"noin 1135","Surrey, England,":"Surrey, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Eskihisar, Merkezefendi, Denizli, Turkey":"Eskihisar, Merkezefendi, Denizli, Turkki","East Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","East Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"East Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Ottoman Empire":"Osmanisches Reich","Türkiye":"Turkki","Paris, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, Ranska"},"fr":{"June 1118–6 January 1148":"juin 1118–6 janvier 1148","–1174":"–1174","1137–1199":"1137–1199","1118–1148":"1118–1148","from 1138":"après 1138","6 Janua